<br>
I do, however, have a huge soft spot in my heart for newbie mages.  In my quests for epic pieces and wandering I've accumulated a lot of different items (especially from SolA -sigh- ).  On my travels to JP or back to Neriak I'll see newbie mages and immediately go up to them, ask to inspect and then give them stuff.  When I see the silk armor or the &quot;spurned initiate trousers&quot; (just think, I was one of those a mere 4 months ago) I'll give them summoned weapons / armor, extra equipment and a nice DS.  Lots of fun.<br>
<br>
The neatest thing though?  Seeing these players you help later on at a higher level.  It is great.  I've made a lot of friends that I've helped and now have regular discussions with them on how to play the mage class to maximum efficiency.  You would be suprised how many people still don't understand how to chain-cast or cannipet.<br>
<br>
Of course, I should probably thank every here at the Magician's Tower for making my first (and favorite character) Mage such an enjoyable experience.  The knowledge that is shared here is better than the time some wizard gave me a 300 plat bonus (at level 5) to buy his new luclin port spells.  =)<br>
<br>
Thanks to all.<br>
<br>
Casala, lvl 54 Elementalist of Saryn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=variathemage>Varia the mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#333333>(1/10/03 7:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8413.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Having to Be Anon When I Go Home</span><hr size=1> I rarely go anon or roleplay.  I don't mind honest questions from mages of any level and chatting with mages that are truly new to EQ can be quite fun.  About two months ago I got a tell from a newbie mage while I was running to Mistmoore to farm some essence for a friend.  The mage had honest questions and most of them were pretty good, so he and I must have spent an hour and a half just chatting about the mage class and the game in general.  Last thing I mentioned to him was this board and suggested he visit it when he had future questions.<br>
<br>
I've only tried the /d for donate trick a few times and have yet to find someone that would fall for it.<br>
<br>
I never give beggers money or items.  I will click combine on research spells for free though if they gather the items.  When I run through a newbie zone, I'll sometimes cast shield of lava on the newbies and if I see a pet, give it a muzzle and a procy weapon (for the HP bonus), then cast a flameshield on the pet.  Oh and focus items if I'm not busy.  Shoot, I wind up summoning focus items for 65s all the time.  I rarely ever get anything in return which is fine, but every once in a while I'm pleasantly surprised when they offer a nice buff or a bit of plat. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108671">Varia Darselai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iradin@themagicianstower>Iradin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(1/10/03 7:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8413.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Having to Be Anon When I Go Home</span><hr size=1> One of my favourite things to do when GFay is filled with newbs is stand at the gates of Felwithe and just shout that I'm casting anything their little heart's desire.  Its great this entire herd of newbs run up.  I make them get in line and I'll cast them what ever tey need.  Focus items, armor.  Anything.  I just started a Ranger, shes level 3 and I was seeing level 5 warriors running around super twinked with at least 4k of equipment on them killing everything in sight so I decided I would help level the playing field for everyone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemag